1
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:51,210
<i>There's something I wanna tell you.</i>

2
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:55,513
<i>After I got shot...</i>

3
00:00:56,689 --> 00:00:59,681
<i>... you wanna know the very first thing</i>
<i>that entered my mind...</i>

4
00:00:59,859 --> 00:01:01,952
<i>... before I blacked out?</i>

5
00:01:05,031 --> 00:01:06,498
<i>Coins.</i>

6
00:01:09,035 --> 00:01:12,903
<i>I'm 8 years old again</i>
<i>on a tour of the U.S. Mint.</i>

7
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:17,003
<i>I'm listening to a guide explain</i>
<i>how coins are made.</i>

8
00:01:17,177 --> 00:01:19,611
<i>How they're punched</i>
<i>out of sheet metal.</i>

9
00:01:19,779 --> 00:01:22,009
<i>How they're rimmed and beveled.</i>

10
00:01:22,182 --> 00:01:24,810
<i>How they are stamped and cleaned.</i>

11
00:01:24,984 --> 00:01:28,681
<i>And how each and every batch</i>
<i>of coins are personally examined.</i>

12
00:01:28,855 --> 00:01:33,121
<i>Just in case any have slipped through</i>
<i>with the slightest imperfection.</i>

13
00:01:33,293 --> 00:01:35,193
<i>That's what popped into my head.</i>

14
00:01:36,663 --> 00:01:39,188
<i>I am a coin</i>
<i>in the United States Army.</i>

15
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:45,560
<i>I was minted in the year 1980.</i>
<i>I've been punched from sheet metal.</i>

16
00:01:45,738 --> 00:01:47,501
<i>I've been stamped and cleaned.</i>

17
00:01:47,674 --> 00:01:50,472
<i>My ridges have been rimmed</i>
<i>and beveled.</i>

18
00:01:52,378 --> 00:01:55,779
<i>But now I have</i>
<i>two small holes in me.</i>

19
00:01:56,316 --> 00:01:58,876
<i>I'm no longer in perfect condition.</i>

20
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:02,414
<i>So there's something else</i>
<i>I wanna tell you.</i>

21
00:02:02,589 --> 00:02:05,183
<i>Right before</i>
<i>everything went black...</i>

22
00:02:05,358 --> 00:02:08,759
<i>... you wanna know the</i>
<i>very last thing that entered my mind?</i>

23
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:12,057
<i>You.</i>

24
00:02:38,525 --> 00:02:41,289
Why not? Because there are
a lot of things you'd be doing.

25
00:02:41,461 --> 00:02:43,429
Just like playing tennis.

26
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:47,899
Wimbledon? I don't know.

27
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:56,999
Just gonna go.
I'm gonna host the thing. Six-thirty.

28
00:02:57,177 --> 00:02:58,667
And you and I could go at 10?

29
00:02:59,445 --> 00:03:00,878
- Oh, shit!
- Oh, no!

30
00:03:01,047 --> 00:03:03,140
- Oh, no, Randy, no!
- I'm sorry.

31
00:03:03,316 --> 00:03:06,149
I'll get it, I'll get it,
I'm on it. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

32
00:03:06,319 --> 00:03:07,445
Okay? I'm on it.

33
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:08,951
My whole life is in that bag.

34
00:03:09,122 --> 00:03:11,352
I got it. I got it.

35
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:35,070
You got it.

36
00:03:42,956 --> 00:03:45,584
Dude. I was gonna get that.

37
00:03:45,758 --> 00:03:47,385
I mean, thanks for jumping in.

38
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,584
Yeah, no problem.

39
00:03:48,761 --> 00:03:51,093
But I mean, hey, I'll take it.

40
00:03:51,631 --> 00:03:53,599
Thank you so much!

41
00:03:54,968 --> 00:03:57,459
Who jumps off a 20-foot pier?

42
00:03:58,471 --> 00:04:02,567
Gosh, I'm a mess.
You are a lifesaver. I'm Savannah.

43
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:04,607
- John.
- John.

44
00:04:04,777 --> 00:04:10,010
Brave man. This is my life in here,
so I owe... I owe you.

45
00:04:10,183 --> 00:04:11,207
Don't worry about it.

46
00:04:11,684 --> 00:04:13,413
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

47
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:15,053
You all have a good night.

48
00:04:15,955 --> 00:04:18,423
Yeah, thanks.
I was in the water for that.

49
00:04:18,992 --> 00:04:21,722
I was seriously getting it for you.

50
00:04:23,129 --> 00:04:24,187
This guy's crazy.

51
00:04:24,364 --> 00:04:28,801
Yeah, no, I swear I'm not. I'm not
stalking you. I just gotta get my board.

52
00:04:28,968 --> 00:04:32,267
- Are you staying here?
- Yeah, yeah, I'm from around here.

53
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:35,999
Hey, John, do you want to...?
My house is right over there.

54
00:04:36,175 --> 00:04:39,838
We were actually going back
right now. Do you want to join us?

55
00:04:40,013 --> 00:04:41,105
We're having a barbecue.

56
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:44,409
It's okay. I don't want to intrude
on y'all. My dad's making dinner.

57
00:04:44,584 --> 00:04:46,074
Okay.

58
00:04:46,252 --> 00:04:50,450
Well, I could at least give you
a beer for the walk home.

59
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:54,687
- Where is it?
- Right over there.

60
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:23,686
- You in the military or something?
- Yeah.

61
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:25,921
Really?

62
00:05:26,092 --> 00:05:28,185
What branch are you in?

63
00:05:28,361 --> 00:05:30,659
Army, Special Forces.

64
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:35,893
Oh, Special Forces.
That's impressive. That's...

65
00:05:37,937 --> 00:05:41,600
Is that like a Special Forces ring they
give you? Is that what it says on it?

66
00:05:41,774 --> 00:05:43,674
It looks nice on you.

67
00:05:43,843 --> 00:05:47,301
Aren't you supposed to be wearing
a hat too? Like a French hat, a beret.

68
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,209
- That's what it's called?
- Randy.

69
00:05:49,382 --> 00:05:50,644
I'm just joking with him.

70
00:05:50,817 --> 00:05:54,548
You shouldn't make fun of a guy
who can kill you with his bare hands.

71
00:05:56,122 --> 00:05:57,885
Big guy.

72
00:05:58,057 --> 00:06:00,355
Rock them, sock them, let's go.

73
00:06:00,526 --> 00:06:02,050
How about that?

74
00:06:03,062 --> 00:06:05,360
You know, I'm gonna go get a beer.

75
00:06:05,531 --> 00:06:08,295
Soldier. Pleasure.

76
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:16,237
I'm sorry about him.
He thinks he likes me.

77
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:18,434
Yeah, I think he likes you too.

78
00:06:18,611 --> 00:06:22,775
No, I'm not his type.
He just doesn't know it yet.

79
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:29,117
What?

80
00:06:30,089 --> 00:06:32,785
Come on, I just think
you're probably everybody's type.

81
00:06:34,694 --> 00:06:36,025
See what I mean?

82
00:06:36,195 --> 00:06:40,825
Is this who I think it is? Alan, Alan.

83
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:44,901
Hey, buddy, I want you to meet John.
John, this is Alan.

84
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,505
- Alan, nice to meet you.
- Say hi.

85
00:06:47,673 --> 00:06:49,641
He's a little bit shy, isn't he?

86
00:06:49,809 --> 00:06:51,299
Hey, where's your dad?

87
00:06:51,477 --> 00:06:55,277
- Over there.
- Two steps behind, as usual.

88
00:06:55,448 --> 00:06:58,849
Sorry, he's like a heat-seeking missile
every time he sees you.

89
00:06:59,018 --> 00:07:00,610
- Oh, hey, I'm Tim.
- John.

90
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:01,913
Sorry.

91
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:03,282
Nice to meet you.

92
00:07:03,456 --> 00:07:05,356
Oh, you Special Forces, huh?

93
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:06,890
Yes, sir.

94
00:07:08,294 --> 00:07:10,228
You stationed out at Fort Bragg?

95
00:07:10,396 --> 00:07:13,126
No, Germany, actually.

96
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:15,665
- Oh, you're on leave.
- Yes, sir.

97
00:07:15,835 --> 00:07:17,302
I hope you're enjoying yourself.

98
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:19,762
Yeah, I think I am.

99
00:07:21,073 --> 00:07:24,440
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to interrupt.
It's nice to meet you though.

100
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:29,013
- Nice to meet you too.
- Come on, son. Let's go.

101
00:07:31,818 --> 00:07:33,285
Let's go.

102
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,817
Hello. Hello, John.

103
00:07:35,988 --> 00:07:37,455
Hello, Alan.

104
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:45,696
- Wow, that was really amazing.
- Yeah?

105
00:07:45,865 --> 00:07:48,527
He never talks to anybody.
Only his family.

106
00:07:48,701 --> 00:07:49,861
He talked to you.

107
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:54,097
Yeah, but I'm practically his family.
I've known him since he was born.

108
00:07:54,273 --> 00:07:55,740
Yeah?

109
00:08:04,183 --> 00:08:05,980
When do you go back?

110
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:07,619
Two weeks.

111
00:08:08,621 --> 00:08:10,919
It must be scary what you do.

112
00:08:12,058 --> 00:08:15,789
Boring mostly.
You know, long stretches of boring.

113
00:08:15,962 --> 00:08:18,522
Occasional flashes of scary.

114
00:08:18,698 --> 00:08:20,563
Full moon tonight.

115
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:27,937
Do you ever notice how big
the moon is when it's rising?

116
00:08:29,242 --> 00:08:32,507
And how little it gets
when it's up in the sky.

117
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:35,670
You know,
that's just your perspective.

118
00:08:35,848 --> 00:08:38,874
It doesn't matter where it is
in the sky or where you are...

119
00:08:39,051 --> 00:08:42,111
...if you hold your hand up
and close one of your eyes...

120
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:45,316
...it's never bigger than your thumb.

121
00:08:50,796 --> 00:08:52,593
Where'd you learn that?

122
00:08:52,765 --> 00:08:54,289
I don't know.

123
00:08:55,067 --> 00:08:56,557
Somewhere.

124
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:07,244
You just made your own fire.

125
00:09:08,414 --> 00:09:10,678
That's very impressive.

126
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:12,410
Very primal.

127
00:09:15,254 --> 00:09:18,553
But you're still not gonna
be able to cook that hotdog, I fear.

128
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:20,555
I fear that as well.

129
00:09:22,028 --> 00:09:24,292
I should probably
be getting going anyways.

130
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:29,326
I'm sorry. I hope you don't get into
too much trouble.

131
00:09:29,502 --> 00:09:31,800
I think it's probably too late for that.

132
00:09:32,638 --> 00:09:33,900
Yeah.

133
00:09:35,207 --> 00:09:36,834
Thank you.

134
00:09:37,009 --> 00:09:40,001
Yeah. No, you're welcome.

135
00:09:43,883 --> 00:09:46,977
Would you wanna maybe
do this again tomorrow night?

136
00:09:47,153 --> 00:09:49,986
Tomorrow is chicken.
I don't think you're gonna wanna try it.

137
00:09:50,156 --> 00:09:53,592
I was kind of hoping maybe we'd let
somebody else do the cooking.

138
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,386
Type of thing.

139
00:09:55,728 --> 00:09:57,992
- Okay.
- Yeah?

140
00:09:59,732 --> 00:10:03,759
So maybe I'll come by around
6 or something?

141
00:10:05,071 --> 00:10:06,868
- Okay.
- All right.

142
00:10:11,377 --> 00:10:13,208
So I'll see you soon, then?

143
00:10:13,379 --> 00:10:14,778
I'll see you soon, then.

144
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:17,780
Yeah. Soon.

145
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:29,954
- Hey.
- Hey, man.

146
00:10:30,429 --> 00:10:33,125
We're headed into town
for some ice cream. You want a ride?

147
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:37,395
No, no, no, it's fine.
I don't mind walking at all. It's fine.

148
00:10:38,371 --> 00:10:39,668
Sure?

149
00:10:41,407 --> 00:10:44,308
- All right. I appreciate it.
- Yeah.

150
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:46,172
Hey, Alan, move on over here.

151
00:10:46,345 --> 00:10:47,642
Here, I'll undo your belt.

152
00:10:50,049 --> 00:10:53,985
Five, six, seven, eight...

153
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:56,519
- So how long are you in town for?
...nine.

154
00:10:56,689 --> 00:10:58,054
We live here year-round now.

155
00:10:58,224 --> 00:11:01,057
Yeah, we were driving down
every weekend anyways...

156
00:11:01,227 --> 00:11:05,527
...so I finally just convinced my wife
this just made the most sense.

157
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,424
- She didn't want ice cream?
- Who?

158
00:11:08,601 --> 00:11:12,162
Oh, my wife. No.

159
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:14,806
No, actually
she's on vacation herself.

160
00:11:14,974 --> 00:11:17,568
White sheep, white sheep,
white sheep.

161
00:11:17,743 --> 00:11:21,076
- It's difficult to take trips together.
- White sheep.

162
00:11:21,847 --> 00:11:24,816
It's fine. We make it work.

163
00:11:26,218 --> 00:11:28,209
I'm up here on the left.

164
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:40,195
Hey, John.

165
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:43,824
For the record,
if you do anything to hurt Savannah...

166
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:46,096
...l'm gonna
have to break something.

167
00:11:46,272 --> 00:11:50,732
Something in your leg.
Some... One of the bones in there.

168
00:11:51,744 --> 00:11:52,870
Okay.

169
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:58,278
It's just I know her father and he would
expect me to say something like that.

170
00:11:58,451 --> 00:12:02,217
It'd just sound a lot more natural
coming out of his mouth.

171
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,753
It sounded fine.

172
00:12:04,256 --> 00:12:06,247
It sounded fine.

173
00:12:06,959 --> 00:12:08,290
- No, it...
- Yes, it did.

174
00:12:08,461 --> 00:12:10,361
- No, it didn't.
- It did. It really did.

175
00:12:10,529 --> 00:12:11,757
It didn't. But thank you.

176
00:12:11,931 --> 00:12:13,865
- It really did.
- You think so?

177
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:15,295
Yeah, it did.

178
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:16,958
Okay.

179
00:12:18,871 --> 00:12:22,204
Hey, don't honk the horn,
it's nighttime.

180
00:12:24,276 --> 00:12:26,744
- Good night, John.
- Good night, Tim.

181
00:12:28,481 --> 00:12:31,417
- Thanks for the ride.
- Yeah, no problem.

182
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:11,185
Hey, Dad, I'm not gonna be able
to stay for dinner.

183
00:13:11,357 --> 00:13:13,621
Well, I made lasagna.

184
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:16,353
I know you made lasagna.
It's Sunday.

185
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:19,692
Can I borrow the car?

186
00:13:28,774 --> 00:13:30,173
Thanks.

187
00:13:33,512 --> 00:13:35,980
- Best seafood you'll ever have.
- Yeah, I know.

188
00:13:36,148 --> 00:13:38,116
- I used to come here all the time.
- Really?

189
00:13:38,284 --> 00:13:41,151
Are you sure you don't wanna go
somewhere, I don't know, nice?

190
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,982
Nice? No, I wanna go
somewhere good.

191
00:13:44,623 --> 00:13:45,988
Okay.

192
00:13:49,195 --> 00:13:51,026
What the hell you doing here?

193
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:56,430
Come on, Steve.
It's been three years already.

194
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,194
I don't want any trouble here.

195
00:13:59,371 --> 00:14:01,839
You're not gonna get any. I promise.

196
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:04,342
All right.

197
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,943
Thank you.

198
00:14:10,349 --> 00:14:12,317
What happened
with that guy out there?

199
00:14:12,484 --> 00:14:14,509
- What guy?
- What's the story with him?

200
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:16,086
- No story.
- Really?

201
00:14:16,255 --> 00:14:17,347
Yeah.

202
00:14:17,823 --> 00:14:19,688
He's an old buddy of mine.

203
00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:24,220
What?

204
00:14:31,103 --> 00:14:33,731
Your dad get mad at you
for coming home late last night?

205
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:38,939
No. He's not really the type
that gets mad.

206
00:14:39,111 --> 00:14:40,772
What kind of guy is he then?

207
00:14:42,915 --> 00:14:44,143
Quiet one?

208
00:14:45,517 --> 00:14:48,918
- Could be worse, I guess.
- I guess.

209
00:14:49,355 --> 00:14:50,913
And your mom?

210
00:14:51,590 --> 00:14:53,820
Nope, just me and my dad.

211
00:14:54,693 --> 00:14:56,854
Did he raise you all by himself?

212
00:14:58,264 --> 00:14:59,663
Yeah.

213
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,562
Why do you wanna know
about my dad?

214
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:04,293
Just curious.

215
00:15:05,204 --> 00:15:07,001
Curious about
where you come from.

216
00:15:13,112 --> 00:15:14,807
I wanna meet your dad.

217
00:15:15,614 --> 00:15:17,013
Tonight.

218
00:15:22,354 --> 00:15:25,585
Look, you're... You're not
gonna get very much out of him.

219
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:28,921
So, I don't know,
just don't take it personally, okay?

220
00:15:32,031 --> 00:15:33,589
Hey, Pop.

221
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:36,459
I got somebody I want you to meet.

222
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:39,265
Hey.

223
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:42,100
- This is Savannah.
- Hi.

224
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:44,742
It's nice to meet you, Mr. Tyree.

225
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:51,340
He... This is my... He collects coins.
He... It's kind of like his big hobby.

226
00:15:51,517 --> 00:15:53,508
This is amazing.

227
00:15:53,686 --> 00:15:57,122
You have so many coins.
How did you get started in all this?

228
00:15:58,390 --> 00:15:59,880
Through John, actually.

229
00:16:01,327 --> 00:16:02,419
Not his thing anymore.

230
00:16:02,594 --> 00:16:06,360
- Hey, we should probably maybe go.
- What is this coin?

231
00:16:06,532 --> 00:16:10,127
That's a Sacagawean mule.

232
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:11,769
It's actually...

233
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:20,377
- Do you want to see some more?
- Absolutely, yes, if you don't mind.

234
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:23,606
- Put this glove on then.
- Thanks.

235
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:29,246
This is a humorous one.
This is a satirical coin.

236
00:16:29,421 --> 00:16:30,445
This is massive.

237
00:16:30,622 --> 00:16:33,352
Yeah, William Jennings Bryan,
when he ran for president...

238
00:16:33,525 --> 00:16:36,688
...he was... He believed in...
No, don't turn it over.

239
00:16:36,862 --> 00:16:38,124
Leave it here.

240
00:16:38,297 --> 00:16:42,358
Do you remember that he had
the free silver policy. You remember.

241
00:16:42,534 --> 00:16:47,665
And McKinley was his opponent
and he's... Wait, here.

242
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:52,277
Now see, that's a real silver dollar.
That's the size of a silver dollar.

243
00:16:52,444 --> 00:16:56,244
And McKinley said that if
Bryan had his way...

244
00:16:56,415 --> 00:16:59,907
...then the silver dollars
would be that big. Yeah.

245
00:17:00,085 --> 00:17:02,110
- That's amazing.
