335
00:25:52,250 --> 00:25:53,444
What?

336
00:25:54,019 --> 00:25:55,816
That's not even funny.

337
00:26:00,025 --> 00:26:01,583
I'm gonna miss you.

338
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:04,189
It's almost over.

339
00:26:04,362 --> 00:26:05,829
No, it's not almost over.

340
00:26:05,997 --> 00:26:07,259
Yes, it is.

341
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:11,392
I leave tomorrow.
I have to go back to school.

342
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:12,628
- So?
- And you.

343
00:26:12,804 --> 00:26:16,331
No, and me nothing.
My commitment's up in 12 months.

344
00:26:17,242 --> 00:26:19,039
And then I'm back. For good.

345
00:26:19,210 --> 00:26:21,974
A lot could happen
in 12 months, John.

346
00:26:22,147 --> 00:26:24,308
You don't think I know that?

347
00:26:25,450 --> 00:26:26,940
I know that.

348
00:26:27,986 --> 00:26:29,920
And I'm not afraid at all.

349
00:26:34,125 --> 00:26:36,423
I promise you...

350
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:39,325
...that it'll all be over
sooner than you think.

351
00:26:40,665 --> 00:26:42,633
Then I'll be back for good.

352
00:26:44,269 --> 00:26:46,237
You promise?

353
00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:50,768
I promise.

354
00:27:11,863 --> 00:27:15,321
I'm probably gonna be out of the Army
way before you're out of school.

355
00:27:16,167 --> 00:27:19,330
Am I gonna be in the audience
when you graduate?

356
00:27:19,504 --> 00:27:22,371
I think I might take
a little longer to graduate.

357
00:27:22,540 --> 00:27:26,704
Been spending so much time
around your dad...

358
00:27:27,045 --> 00:27:30,879
...and I think now
I want to teach special education.

359
00:27:31,049 --> 00:27:33,643
- You don't say.
- I don't know why it's taken me...

360
00:27:33,818 --> 00:27:38,915
...so long to realize. I mean,
I've lived next to Alan my whole life...

361
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:42,856
I'm sorry, back up. What does
that have to do with my dad?

362
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:48,694
Well, there's...

363
00:27:49,801 --> 00:27:53,703
I mean, there's an explanation
for why he is the way he is.

364
00:27:55,607 --> 00:27:57,575
Forget it. Never mind.

365
00:27:57,742 --> 00:27:59,801
- No, no, no.
- No, let's go. Come here.

366
00:27:59,978 --> 00:28:02,742
What?
So, just, what were you saying?

367
00:28:07,052 --> 00:28:09,680
I grew up next to a kid with autism.

368
00:28:10,255 --> 00:28:12,450
- I have a frame of reference.
- Whoa, autistic?

369
00:28:12,624 --> 00:28:16,253
You saying my dad's like Alan?
You're saying my dad's retarded?

370
00:28:16,428 --> 00:28:19,795
No, Alan's not retarded, John.
He's autistic.

371
00:28:19,964 --> 00:28:22,762
There are milder forms of it
and these things go undiagnosed.

372
00:28:22,934 --> 00:28:26,495
Is this what you've been doing?
You've just been studying my dad?

373
00:28:26,671 --> 00:28:28,605
No. How could you even say that?

374
00:28:28,773 --> 00:28:32,072
I've lived with my dad my entire life.
Put up with him my entire life.

375
00:28:32,243 --> 00:28:34,541
You think I don't know
that he's not normal?

376
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:36,308
Yeah?

377
00:28:36,481 --> 00:28:39,348
You think I need you to tell me
he's not normal?

378
00:28:42,187 --> 00:28:43,552
Yeah.

379
00:28:48,626 --> 00:28:51,686
Hey, soldier, leaving so soon, huh?

380
00:28:51,863 --> 00:28:55,094
Here, have a beer. It's on me.

381
00:28:55,266 --> 00:28:57,826
