433
00:33:06,918 --> 00:33:09,751
And I just wanted
to make sure that, you know...

434
00:33:09,921 --> 00:33:11,684
Make sure that what?

435
00:33:12,857 --> 00:33:15,291
I made you a promise, didn't I?

436
00:33:16,060 --> 00:33:17,425
Yeah.

437
00:33:20,164 --> 00:33:24,362
You wrote your first note
so I wrote mine.

438
00:33:26,104 --> 00:33:28,299
Don't read it now. Wait till I'm gone.

439
00:33:28,473 --> 00:33:29,804
Okay.

440
00:33:30,975 --> 00:33:34,741
- Hey, can you...? You hungry?
- Yes.

441
00:33:34,912 --> 00:33:38,939
Yeah? My dad made
a little extra for you.

442
00:33:39,117 --> 00:33:40,982
You know, it's Sunday.

443
00:33:41,152 --> 00:33:42,380
Okay.

444
00:33:42,553 --> 00:33:44,521
- I can only stay a little while.
- I know.

445
00:33:44,689 --> 00:33:45,917
Come on.

446
00:33:50,828 --> 00:33:52,295
<i>Dear John...</i>

447
00:33:53,564 --> 00:33:55,555
<i>... two weeks together...</i>

448
00:33:55,733 --> 00:33:57,758
<i>... that's all it took.</i>

449
00:34:00,304 --> 00:34:03,705
<i>Two weeks for me</i>
<i>to fall in love with you.</i>

450
00:34:16,954 --> 00:34:19,354
<i>Now we have one year apart.</i>

451
00:34:20,458 --> 00:34:24,258
<i>But what's one year apart</i>
<i>after two weeks like that together?</i>

452
00:34:35,006 --> 00:34:36,473
- All right, Pop.
- Okay.

453
00:34:36,641 --> 00:34:38,632
I gotta go.

454
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:41,176
- You be good, okay?
- Okay.

455
00:34:41,345 --> 00:34:42,835
So...

456
00:34:43,815 --> 00:34:46,340
- We're good. All right. See you later.
- Okay.

457
00:34:56,294 --> 00:34:58,262
<i>You made me a promise.</i>

458
00:34:58,429 --> 00:35:00,454
<i>A promise I know you'll keep.</i>

459
00:35:01,032 --> 00:35:05,492
<i>So I only want one more promise from</i>
<i>you during this time we spend apart.</i>

460
00:35:06,370 --> 00:35:08,235
<i>Tell me everything.</i>

461
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:12,175
<i>Write it all down, John.</i>
<i>Scribble it in a notebook.</i>

462
00:35:12,343 --> 00:35:14,811
<i>Type it out, e-mail it to me...</i>

463
00:35:15,613 --> 00:35:18,411
<i>... I don't care,</i>
<i>but I wanna know everything.</i>

464
00:35:20,551 --> 00:35:25,181
<i>Then we'll be with each other all the</i>
<i>time even if we're not with each other.</i>

465
00:35:26,390 --> 00:35:30,554
<i>That way before we know it,</i>
<i>I'll see you soon, then.</i>

466
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:42,872
- What's up, girls?
- Johnny!

467
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:44,200
What up, man?

468
00:35:44,375 --> 00:35:45,967
- Hey, there he is.
- Look who it is.

469
00:35:46,144 --> 00:35:48,510
- Welcome back, John.
- Look at you.

470
00:35:48,679 --> 00:35:50,579
Welcome back.
Take a look at your voucher.

471
00:35:50,748 --> 00:35:52,306
All right.

472
00:35:53,451 --> 00:35:55,316
How was Atlantic City, man?

473
00:35:58,189 --> 00:36:01,420
No, laugh it up. That's great.
Yeah. That's the one thing I ask him.

474
00:36:01,592 --> 00:36:03,492
I didn't say.
First time I've seen him.

475
00:36:03,661 --> 00:36:06,152
- Wouldn't ask if you didn't know.
- How could he know?

476
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:08,355
Don't even bother unpacking, guys.

477
00:36:08,533 --> 00:36:12,196
We move out bright and early.
Enjoy.

478
00:36:13,638 --> 00:36:15,572
Well, I'm excited.

479
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:27,278
<i>Dear Savannah, I promise.</i>
<i>I promise I'll see you soon, then.</i>

480
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:30,411
<i>I promise I'll write all the time.</i>

481
00:36:30,588 --> 00:36:32,920
<i>I promise I'll tell you everything.</i>

482
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:40,324
<i>Be patient with me, it may take a while</i>
<i>for these letters to get back to you.</i>

483
00:36:41,566 --> 00:36:44,228
<i>We've already been deployed</i>
<i>out on a mission.</i>

484
00:36:46,504 --> 00:36:49,530
Come on, soldier, move it, move it.
Let's go!

485
00:36:51,976 --> 00:36:57,039
<i>The problem is we can't exactly</i>
<i>use the local postal system here.</i>

