522
00:39:38,075 --> 00:39:40,066
Are you hungry?

523
00:39:40,878 --> 00:39:43,312
<i>Where they can ride horses</i>
<i>as much as they want.</i>

524
00:39:43,481 --> 00:39:45,540
Are you hungry?

525
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:50,411
<i>For once in their life, a place where</i>
<i>they won't have to worry about a thing.</i>

526
00:39:51,489 --> 00:39:54,117
<i>What do you think?</i>
<i>Pipe dream, huh?</i>

527
00:39:54,291 --> 00:39:56,225
<i>No, it's not a pipe dream.</i>

528
00:39:56,394 --> 00:39:58,555
<i>It's a perfect dream.</i>

529
00:40:00,798 --> 00:40:03,926
Erget. Merry Christmas.

530
00:40:04,101 --> 00:40:07,229
John, to a Mr. John Tyree.

531
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:08,497
- Shut up, man.
- Seven?

532
00:40:08,672 --> 00:40:11,275
- Stop moving around.
- Can I keep this one?

533
00:40:11,342 --> 00:40:13,572
<i>Letter Number 33.</i>

534
00:40:13,744 --> 00:40:18,010
<i>Dear Savannah, the good news is</i>
<i>we've been sent somewhere new.</i>

535
00:40:18,182 --> 00:40:20,912
<i>Although I can't tell you</i>
<i>where that is either.</i>

536
00:40:21,085 --> 00:40:25,545
<i>The bad news is, this place actually</i>
<i>makes me miss the old place.</i>

537
00:40:25,723 --> 00:40:28,624
