<i>which makes me think of you.</i>

538
00:40:28,793 --> 00:40:32,991
<i>Because I know that no matter what</i>
<i>I'm doing, no matter where I am...</i>

539
00:40:33,164 --> 00:40:36,258
<i>... this moon will always be</i>
<i>the same size as yours.</i>

540
00:40:36,434 --> 00:40:37,992
<i>Half a world away.</i>

541
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:40,627
<i>Dear John...</i>

542
00:40:40,805 --> 00:40:43,933
<i>... most nights I fall asleep</i>
<i>worrying about you.</i>

543
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:46,406
<i>Wondering where</i>
<i>you may be out there.</i>

544
00:40:48,412 --> 00:40:50,505
<i>Not tonight.</i>

545
00:40:50,681 --> 00:40:52,740
<i>Tonight you're here with me.</i>

546
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:59,321
<i>I visited your dad yesterday.</i>

547
00:41:00,424 --> 00:41:04,520
<i>Summer's almost over and I wanted to</i>
<i>see him before I went back to school.</i>

548
00:41:04,695 --> 00:41:05,787
<i>I hope that's okay.</i>

549
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:07,157
Hey.

550
00:41:07,331 --> 00:41:08,662
I made you a pie.

551
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:12,899
<i>He made me dinner.</i>
<i>It was Sunday so we had lasagna.</i>

552
00:41:13,070 --> 00:41:17,632
<i>And I got him talking about his coins.</i>
<i>So we had plenty of conversation.</i>

553
00:41:17,808 --> 00:41:21,938
This one is kind of a cull,
a coin that's in really bad shape.

554
00:41:22,112 --> 00:41:25,309
- Worthless to most collectors.
- But not to you.

555
00:41:25,783 --> 00:41:27,444
No, not to me.

556
00:41:27,618 --> 00:41:29,381
What is your favorite coin?

557
00:41:30,287 --> 00:41:34,849
Out of all the coins that you have,
what is your absolute favorite coin?

558
00:41:35,292 --> 00:41:36,816
Do you have one?

559
00:41:46,904 --> 00:41:49,304
'Seventy-eight Jefferson mule.

560
00:41:50,407 --> 00:41:52,204
That'd be my favorite.

561
00:41:52,743 --> 00:41:54,608
Definitely.

562
00:41:55,079 --> 00:41:58,344
Why? Is it worth the most?

563
00:41:58,849 --> 00:42:01,477
Well, it's worth a lot, not the most.

564
00:42:01,652 --> 00:42:03,552
But, you know...

565
00:42:04,221 --> 00:42:05,882
What's the story behind it?

566
00:42:12,096 --> 00:42:13,120
Here's one...

567
00:42:13,297 --> 00:42:17,063
<i>So I'll ask you instead, John,</i>
<i>wherever you may be.</i>

568
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:27,577
<i>Dear Savannah, only because</i>
<i>I promised to tell you everything.</i>

569
00:42:28,979 --> 00:42:30,640
Thank you.

570
00:42:30,814 --> 00:42:34,306
<i>When I was 7 years old,</i>
<i>I bought an ice cream cone.</i>

571
00:42:35,886 --> 00:42:40,050
<i>On the way home, I noticed one of</i>
<i>the pennies wasn't actually a penny.</i>

572
00:42:53,337 --> 00:42:54,861
I don't know.

573
00:42:56,807 --> 00:43:00,334
I don't know.
Never seen anything like it.

574
00:43:01,345 --> 00:43:03,313
Did you find this, son?

575
00:43:04,548 --> 00:43:05,640
Yeah?

576
00:43:06,650 --> 00:43:08,117
No, it's a mule.

577
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:12,887
- It's a what?
- A mule. An error coin.

578
00:43:13,057 --> 00:43:14,888
Every now and then
they make mistakes...

579
00:43:15,059 --> 00:43:17,755
...batch accidentally slips through,
this thing...

580
00:43:17,928 --> 00:43:22,729
...head's a nickel, tail's a penny. Mule.
Really more of a novelty than anything.

581
00:43:22,900 --> 00:43:25,391
<i>Remember the horse sense</i>
<i>you were talking about?</i>

582
00:43:25,569 --> 00:43:27,594
- The kid found it
I will buy it anyway.

583
00:43:27,771 --> 00:43:29,398
Twenty bucks.

584
00:43:32,076 --> 00:43:34,601
- No, thank you.
- <i>Well, my dad has it too.</i>

585
00:43:34,778 --> 00:43:36,939
Now, wait a minute. Hang on.

586
00:43:37,114 --> 00:43:39,309
Let me take another look
at that real quick.

587
00:43:42,786 --> 00:43:44,276
John, let's go.

588
00:43:44,455 --> 00:43:46,047
I'll be damned.

589
00:43:46,824 --> 00:43:49,384
- Do you know what this is?
- No.

590
00:43:58,035 --> 00:43:59,696
Look at that.

591
00:43:59,870 --> 00:44:01,235
That's your coin.

592
00:44:01,405 --> 00:44:02,895
You want my advice?

593
00:44:03,073 --> 00:44:04,734
Dad to Dad?

594
00:44:04,908 --> 00:44:06,239
Keep it.

595
00:44:06,410 --> 00:44:09,140
Hold on to it.
Pass it down to your son.

596
00:44:09,313 --> 00:44:12,214
Let him pass it to his son
and on and on, I'll tell you what...

597
00:44:12,383 --> 00:44:16,285
...30, 40, a hundred years
from now...

598
00:44:16,954 --> 00:44:20,082
...you're gonna have something
worth a whole lot more than $4000.

599
00:44:20,257 --> 00:44:21,986
I promise you.

600
00:44:23,627 --> 00:44:25,094
Hey.

601
00:44:25,262 --> 00:44:26,820
Do you want to keep it?

602
00:44:29,566 --> 00:44:31,830
- Good for you.
- Thank you. Thank you.

603
00:44:33,170 --> 00:44:35,900
<i>At first I loved chasing after</i>
<i>those mules with my father.</i>

604
00:44:36,073 --> 00:44:38,405
<i>We finally had something</i>
<i>to talk about.</i>

605
00:44:38,575 --> 00:44:41,009
<i>You know, something</i>
<i>we could do together.</i>

606
00:44:41,845 --> 00:44:45,212
<i>But he became obsessed with them.</i>
<i>You know how he is.</i>

607
00:44:45,849 --> 00:44:49,285
<i>And then I became a teenager</i>
<i>and you know how I am.</i>

608
00:44:49,453 --> 00:44:52,513
All the way up to Wooster
for another coin show. I'm just...

609
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:54,715
No, I'm not doing that.

610
00:44:54,892 --> 00:44:57,360
You're going to one
every weekend now.

611
00:44:58,629 --> 00:45:02,190
Oh, that's good.
I love warm milk. That's nice.

612
00:45:02,366 --> 00:45:06,359
You spend all of our money on coins.
Get a fricking fridge that works.

613
00:45:14,211 --> 00:45:17,874
<i>Eventually he stopped talking</i>
<i>about coins with me altogether.</i>

614
00:45:19,249 --> 00:45:20,443
<i>And when that happened...</i>

615
00:45:20,617 --> 00:45:24,053
<i>... we found there wasn't all that much</i>
<i>left to talk about.</i>

616
00:45:29,927 --> 00:45:32,361
<i>So that's the story.</i>

617
00:45:34,098 --> 00:45:36,033
<i>I miss you so much it hurts.</i>

618
00:45:38,102 --> 00:45:39,933
Sorry, sorry.

619
00:45:40,871 --> 00:45:43,601
Oh, my God.
My brother was in the towers.

620
00:45:43,774 --> 00:45:47,301
- I love you too, babe.
- Please call me as soon as you can.

621
00:45:52,449 --> 00:45:56,249
- Susan. Susan, is my dad there?
- Just calm down.

622
00:46:32,589 --> 00:46:34,386
All right, fellas, here's the deal.

623
00:46:34,558 --> 00:46:36,822
Requesting permission
to extend my tour, sir.

624
00:46:36,994 --> 00:46:38,859
Requesting permission
to extend, sir.

625
00:46:39,029 --> 00:46:41,293
Requesting permission
to extend as well, sir.

626
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:43,160
Requesting permission
to extend, sir.

627
00:46:43,333 --> 00:46:45,631
Requesting permission
to extend as well, sir.

628
00:46:45,803 --> 00:46:49,705
Okay, guys, listen. We're gonna get
our orders from Operations on Monday.

629
00:46:49,873 --> 00:46:53,707
Before we do anything rash, let's take
the weekend to mull this over, all right?

630
00:46:53,877 --> 00:46:55,708
I got a wife and kids to think about.

631
00:46:56,113 --> 00:46:58,775
Nobody's asking you
to stay on too, captain.

632
00:46:58,949 --> 00:47:01,008
Yeah, you are. This is my team.

633
00:47:01,185 --> 00:47:02,652
Where you go, I go.

634
00:47:02,820 --> 00:47:05,186
Where we go, we all go.

635
00:47:05,355 --> 00:47:08,722
